# Compliance Checklist AgriTech Platform 

## Overview

This checklist defines key compliance controls required for a digital AgriTech platform, integrating governance, risk, and regulatory requirements aligned with Colombian law and GDPR.

---

## 1. Governance & Accountability

- [ ] Define Data Controller and responsibilities.
- [ ] Assign Data Protection Officer if applicable.
- [ ] Establish internal data protection policies.
- [ ] Maintain records of processing activities (ROPA)
- [ ] Implement accountability principle (GDPR)

---

## 2. Legal Compliance (Colombia & GDPR)

- [ ] Identify applicable regulations (Law 1581, GDPR).
- [ ] Ensure lawful basis for data processing.
- [ ] Obtain valid user consent mechanisms.
- [ ] Register databases with SIC if required.
- [ ] Implement privacy-by-design principles.

---

## 3. Data Collection & Minimization

- [ ] Collect only necessary data.
- [ ] Define clear purposes for data collection.
- [ ] Avoid excessive or unrelated data processing.
- [ ] Validate data accuracy and relevance.

---

## 4. User Rights Management

- [ ] Enable access to personal data.
- [ ] Allow correction and updates.
- [ ] Provide data deletion mechanisms.
- [ ] Enable consent withdrawal.
- [ ] Implement GDPR rights (portability, restriction).

---

## 5. Security Controls

- [ ] Encrypt data in transit and at rest.
- [ ] Implement access control (role-based).
- [ ] Monitor unauthorized access attempts.
- [ ] Conduct periodic security assessments.
- [ ] Implement secure coding practices.

---

## 6. AI & Automated Processing

- [ ] Identify AI-driven processes.
- [ ] Inform users about automated decision-making.
- [ ] Implement human oversight mechanisms.
- [ ] Validate accuracy of AI outputs.
- [ ] Document AI risks and limitations.

---

## 7. Geolocation & Sensitive Data

- [ ] Justify use of geolocation data.
- [ ] Implement explicit consent mechanisms.
- [ ] Apply additional safeguards for sensitive data.
- [ ] Limit access to high-risk data categories.

---

## 8. Third-Party & Vendor Management

- [ ] Identify all third-party providers.
- [ ] Evaluate vendor security and compliance.
- [ ] Sign data processing agreements (DPA).
- [ ] Monitor third-party data handling practices.
- [ ] Control API integrations and data sharing.

---

## 9. Data Transfers

- [ ] Identify international data transfers.
- [ ] Implement safeguards (SCCs or equivalents).
- [ ] Assess transfer risks.
- [ ] Ensure compliance with local regulations.

---

## 10. Data Retention & Deletion

- [ ] Define data retention periods.
- [ ] Implement secure deletion mechanisms.
- [ ] Avoid indefinite data storage.
- [ ] Document retention policies.

---

## 11. Incident Response & Breach Management

- [ ] Establish incident response plan.
- [ ] Detect and classify security incidents.
- [ ] Notify authorities (SIC / GDPR requirements).
- [ ] Notify affected users when required.
- [ ] Document and review incidents.

---

## 12. Monitoring & Continuous Compliance

- [ ] Conduct periodic compliance audits.
- [ ] Update policies and controls regularly.
- [ ] Track regulatory changes.
- [ ] Train staff on data protection practices.

---
